<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     09-19 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0124</SECOND>
<HEAD>New Correspondent Named in Johnson City, Tenn.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leslie Lloyd, a newswoman in the
Philadelphia bureau of The Associated Press, has been named AP
correspondent in Johnson City, Tenn.
   The appointment was announced Monday by Nashville Chief of Bureau
Kent Flanagan.
   Ms. Lloyd, 27, joined the AP in 1988 and worked in Atlanta before
moving to Philadelphia later that year. Previously, she worked at
The Union (S.C.) Daily Times and in the Aiken, S.C., bureau of The
Augusta (Ga.) Chronicle-Herald.
   She is a native of Little Rock, Ark., and a graduate of the
University of Georgia.
   In Johnson City, she succeeds Leanne Waxman, who has been
promoted to the General Desk in New York.
</TEXT>
