<FIRST>r w PM-CrashTape-Excerpts     09-19 0477</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Crash Tape-Excerpts,0536</SECOND>
<HEAD>Excerpts of United 232's Cockpit Conversation</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Crash Tape</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are portions of the transcript of United
Flight 232's cockpit voice recorder released Monday by the National
Transportation Safety Board. The board put unclear words in
parentheses and deleted expletives.
   At 30 minutes before landing:
   Unidentified voice: ``Come on baby, come on baby.''
   First Officer William Records: ``What's the hydraulic quantity?''
   Second Officer Dudley Dvorak: ``Down to Zero.''
   Records: ``On all of them?''
   Dvorak: ``All of them.''
   Capt. Alfred Haynes: ``You got ahold of SAM (United's System
Airline Maintenance base in San Francisco)?''
   Dvorak: ``Yeah, I've talked to 'im.''
   Haynes: ``What's he saying?''
   Dvorak: ``He's not telling me anything.''
   Haynes: ``We're not gonna make the runway, fellas. We're gonna
have to ditch this son of a (expletive deleted) and hope for the
best.''
</TEXT>
<NOTE>___</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   At 10 minutes:
   Haynes: ``Level up here.''
   Haynes (after talking on radio:) ``Right turn, he said ... Well,
momma, we'll (make or miss) those baseball games after all.''
   Records: ``Are you in good and tight?
   Training officer Dennis Fitch (operating throttles): ``I'm not in
at all, Bill.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   At 9 minutes:
   Haynes: ``Back, back.''
   Fitch: ``Hold this thing level if you can.''
   Haynes: ``Level, baby, level, level.''
   Dvorak: ``We're turning now.''
   Unidentified: ``More power, more power, give 'em more power.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   At 7 minutes:
   Haynes: ``Come back, come back, all the way back.''
   Unidentified, apparently Fitch: ``I can't handle that steep of
bank, can't handle that steep of bank ... Dammit, wish we hadn't put
that gear down.''
   Unidentified: ``Ah, well. (I didn't ... you know.)''
   Unidentified: ``We don't know.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   At 6 minutes:
   Haynes: ``Want to keep turnin' right, want to go to the airport.''
   Fitch: ``You want to go to the airport?''
   Haynes: ``I want to get as close to the airport as we can.''
   Fitch: ``Okay.''
   Haynes: ``(If we have to set this thing in the dirt, we set it in
the dirt.'')
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   At 4 minutes:
   Haynes: ``Back, back, back, back ... forward, forward, forward
... Won't this be a fun landing?''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   At 2 minutes:
   Fitch: ``I got the runway if you don't''
   Haynes: ``I don't. Come back, come back.''
   Fitch: ``It's off to the right.''
   Haynes: ``Right there, right there.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   The last 30 seconds:
   Haynes: ``Stop your turn... Ease the power back, ease the power
back.''
   Records: ``Maybe you can pull 'em all the way off.''
   Haynes: ``Left turns, left turns ... close the throttles.''
   Records: ``Close 'em off.''
   Haynes: ``Right turn, close the throttles.''
   Records: ``Pull 'em (all) off.''
   Fitch: ``Nah, I can't pull 'em off or we'll lose it. That's
what's turnin' ya.''
   Unidentified: ``Okay.''
   Unidentified: ``Okay.''
   Records: ``Left, Al. Left throttle, left, left, left, left, left,
left, left, left, left, left.''
   Unidentified: ``We're (turnin', turnin', turnin' or tryin',
tryin', tryin'.)
   Unidentified: ``God.''
   Sound of impact.
</TEXT>
