<SECOND>PM-BRF--Gunman Arrested,0158</SECOND>
<HEAD>Armed Man Arrested, Tragedy Averted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former employee armed with a revolver and five
Molotov cocktails was arrested outside Northwestern Memorial
Hospital, where he intended to stage a massacre, police said.
   Connell Hardy, 31, was angry about his forced resignation last
year as emergency room clerk, police said.
   ``We learned from him that he intended to go in and kill
everybody in the hospital,'' said police Lt. Patrick Logan.
   Hardy was armed with a .357-caliber Magnum, more than 40 rounds
of ammunition, and five bottles of alcohol rigged so they could be
lit and thrown, authorities said.
   Police said Hardy walked into the American Bar Association
offices on Monday after mistaking it for the hospital's offices. He
was given directions at the ABA but was stopped by police before
reaching the hospital.
   Hardy was being held in a lockup while investigators determined
the specific charges, police said.
