<HEAD>President's Mother Admitted to Hospital With Pneumonia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENWICH, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush's 88-year-old mother was
admitted to a hospital for pneumonia, officials said.
   Dorothy Walker Bush was in stable condition and was expected to
improve, said Alixe Glen, a White House spokeswoman.
   She said the president, who was traveling in the West on Monday,
was monitoring his mother's condition through White House physician
