nationally. It doesn't bode well,'' Schultz said.
   One mayoral candidate, Sharon Pratt Dixon, called on Barry not to
seek re-election, saying the incident shows he is ``essentially
politically impotent.''
   Barry, whose links to a convicted drug dealer are under federal
investigation, has repeatedly denied ever using drugs.
   Officials said about 275,000 people attended the outdoor festival.
