<FIRST>r a PM-BoiledBody     09-19 0172</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Boiled Body,0177</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police: Spurned Boyfriend Arrested in Body Boiling of Girlfriend</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A short-order cook was charged with murder after
police found boiled and peeled parts of his girlfriend's body in a
bus terminal storage compartment.
   Daniel Rakowitz, 28, was arrested Monday. The victim, a
26-year-old dancer, was not immediately identified.
   Deputy Chief Ronald Fenrich said the victim's skull and some
bones were discovered Monday. The remains were in a five-gallon
container and mixed with cat box filler, said Sgt. John Clifford, a
police spokesman.
   ``He basically boiled the body and flushed the skin down the
toilet,'' Clifford said.
   Police said they were investigating the possibility of
cannibalism.
   The victim, believed to have been a native of Switzerland, broke
off her relationship with Rakowitz, police said. The woman was
beaten and stabbed and her body was kept in the couple's apartment
for about a week, where it was dismembered, Fenrich said.
   ``The relationship had gone sour and she wanted other people to
occupy the apartment,'' Fenrich said.
