<HEAD>South Africa Bans Video Featuring Exotic Male Dancers From U.S.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A film company said Tuesday
that government censors have banned a video of the Chippendales, a
troupe of male exotic dancers from the United States who are drawing
capacity crowds at a resort in a black homeland.
   Videovision Enterprises said in a statement that censors declared
the video ``lust-provoking'' and ``offensive.''
   The company said it had acquired rights to distribute the video,
entitled ``Tall, Dark and Handsome,'' because of the Chippendales'
current box-office success at Sun City, a sports-and-gambling resort
in the tribal homeland of Bophuthatswana.
   The South African censors' rulings have no authority in
Bophuthatswana and three other nominally independent homelands.
   Hazel Feldman, entertainment director at Sun City, said she was
surprised by the censors' decision.
   ``There is nothing salacious about the Chippendales' show,'' she
said. ``It is good, clean, wholesome fun.''
   Sun City regularly offers nude revues featuring female dancers.
The Chippendales are the first all-male troupe to perform a
comparable revue, and have been playing to sold-out houses.
