<HEAD>Five-Day Ordeal Makes Cool Cat Nice</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEVERNA PARK, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five sweltering days pinned inside a box
spring on a moving truck turned the once-standoffish Pippen the cat
into a cuddly pet.
   The calico owned by Sandy Zywica and her husband, Richard, was
found with her paws stuck in the springs after the couple's
belongings arrived from their Kenosha, Wis., home at new digs in
Severna Park.
   The cat had been missed, but checks of her favorite spots failed
to turn her up. She was pulled from the truck Aug. 22 to the claps
of moving men.
   ``She's very standoffish and that's what got her into trouble,''
Mrs. Zywica said. ``She just never was a friendly cat.''
   But that was before Pippen's ordeal, which left her tired but
healthy after a brief recovery. Now, she cuddles and rubs against
her owners.
   ``She would have never done this before,'' Mrs. Zywica said.
