<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--India-Accident     09-19 0098</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--India-Accident,0099</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bus Runs Over Children in India, Killing 11</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus plowed into a group of children
outside a roadside temple in southern India, killing 11 of them, it
was reported Tuesday.
   The accident occurred when the bus driver lost control of the
vehicle while overtaking a motor scooter, Press Trust of India said.
   Six children were killed immediately, and five died in a
hospital, the news agency said. The children had gathered for a
feast at the temple in Arupukottai village in southern Tamil Nadu
state, the news agency said.
</TEXT>
