<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Greece-Earthquake     09-19 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Greece-Earthquake,0129</SECOND>
<HEAD>Strong Tremor Shakes Northern Greece</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An earthquake shook northwestern Greece on
Tuesday, but no injuries or damage were reported, authorities said.
   The Athens Geodynamic Institute said the quake, which occurred at
10:57 a.m., measured 4.9 on the Richter scale and its epicenter was
165 miles northwest of Athens in the Ioannina area.
   Inhabitants within a 40-mile radius of the epicenter felt the
tremor, a spokesman for the institute said.
   Police contacted by telephone in Ioannina reported residents of
the city remained calm despite the strength of the jolt.
   The Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an
earthquake as measured by ground motion recorded on a seismograph.
   A magnitude 5 earthquake can cause considerable damage.
</TEXT>
