<HEAD>Bush Expresses Sympathy for Victims of Hurricane</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Hugo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPOKANE, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush expressed his sympathy today
for victims of the deadly hurricane that struck Puerto Rico, the
Virgin Islands and the Caribbean and said the federal government is
dispatching a team to help in the rescue efforts.
   White House press secretary Marlin Fitzwater issued a statement
here on the hurricane at the president's last stop on a two-day
Western trip to publicize his environmental proposals.
   Fitzwater said:
   ``The president today expressed concern and sympathy for the
death and destruction wreaked on the Virgin Islands and Puerto Rico
and throughout the Caribbean by Hurricane Huge. The federal
government stands ready to respond promptly and fully.''
