<HEAD>Sudan, Central Africa Restore Relations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KHARTOUM, Sudan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sudan has re-established diplomatic
relations with the Central African republic, the official Sudan News
Agency reported Tuesday.
   The Central African republic severed relations with Sudan earlier
this year when the Khartoum government denied permission for a plane
carrying Central African President Andre Kolinga to use its air
space en route to Israel.
   The agency said the decision was announced by Brig. Tigani Adam
al-Tahir, a member of the ruling 15-man military junta that came to
power June 30.
