during a daylong standoff that ended with his surrender after nine
hours, authorities said.
   No injuries were reported.
   Dustin Pierce, a 17-year-old, straight-A student, was detained by
police Monday evening after he released his last two hostages, laid
down three guns and surrendered. Charges were not immediately filed.
