<TEXT>
   Manufacturers Hanover Corp. announced a major
restructuring that includes selling 60 percent of its CIT Group
financial services unit to Japanese banking giant Dai-Ichi Kangyo
Bank Ltd. and adding $950 million to its loan-loss reserves to cover
shaky Third World debt.
   The New York-based bank also said Monday it would issue up to
$500 million in new common stock before year's end.
