<HEAD>Ford's Car of the Year Added to Incentive List</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co.'s 1989 Thunderbird SC,
Motor Trend magazine's ``Car of the Year,'' is now on the list of
vehicles for which the automaker offers incentives.
   Buyers of the Thunderbird SC, which stands for super coupe, and
the Mercury Cougar XR-7, both built in Ford's Lorain, Ohio, plant,
will receive a $1,500 rebate or a choice of low-interest financing
programs, the automaker said.
   There weren't any incentives on those cars until Monday.
   Ford also boosted incentives to $750 from $500 for the Probe GL
and LX models and to $1,000 from $500 for the Probe GT.
   The new programs expire Oct. 4. Ford last week introduced its
line of cars and trucks for the 1990 model year.
