<HEAD>London Shares Close Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with close</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were moderately lower Tuesday.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed 12.3
points, or 0.5 percent, lower at 2361.5, nearly 10 points above a
session low of 2351.4 and off the intraday high of 2379.4.
   Volume was 393.5 million shares, up from 310.2 million Monday.
   Dealers said market makers were active in liquidating holdings in
a broad array of shares, positions they had built up in recent weeks
anticipating the stock index would test its all-time high of 2443.4.
   A late announcement by Ford Motor Co. that it may bid for a
friendly stake in Jaguar PLC injected some fresh confidence into
what has largely been a takeover-driven market, dealers said.
   But the market didn't react aggressively outside of bidding
Jaguar shares up 62 pence to close at 467 pence, or $7.33.
