<FIRST>r f AM-BoeingOrder     09-19 0109</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Boeing Order,0114</SECOND>
<HEAD>AirMalta Orders Three Boeing Jets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   AirMalta has ordered three Boeing 737-500
jetliners and spare parts in a deal valued at about $90 million,
Boeing Co. said Tuesday.
   AirMalta, the national flag carrier of Malta, also took options
on three more of the twinjets.
   The jets ordered by AirMalta will carry about 125 passengers in a
single class. The first is to be delivered in June 1993.
   The 737-500 is the newest and smallest of the 737 family. It is
in flight testing, with Federal Aviation Administration
certification expected in March 1990.
   All together, seventeen airline customers have ordered 171 of the
737-500s.
</TEXT>
