<FILEID>AP-NR-09-19-89 2023EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-Chrysler     09-19 0311</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Chrysler,0323</SECOND>
<HEAD>Large Chrysler Cars To Be Rounder in Three Years</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By FREDERICK STANDISH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Auto Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HIGHLAND PARK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp.'s new line of boxy
luxury cars will be replaced beginning in 1993 by rounder models,
company executives said Tuesday.
   The comments came as Chrysler introduced its 1990 cars, including
a new Imperial, a nameplate asbent for seven years.
   Chrysler will begin its LH large-and luxury-car program for the
1993 model year, with four-door, front-wheel-drive models.
Manufacturing capability will permit two-door and rear-wheel-drive
models, Chrysler spokesman Tom Kowaleski said.
   Replacements of the company's line of luxury cars are part of
Chrysler's plans, said Tom Pappert, vice president for sales for the
nation's No. 3 automaker.
   Officials said the company planned to offer more rounded luxury
cars in the future. This year, Ford Motor Co. introduced a rounder
Lincoln Town Car.
   When asked if Chrysler planned to sell two styles of large cars,
Pappert, standing about 20 feet from a new Imperial, said, ``I think
we aren't going to keep two.''
   The four-door 1990 Chrysler Imperial revives a nameplate last
seen in the 1983 model year on a two-door model. The last Imperial
four-door was for the 1975 model year.
   Also Tuesday, Dodge Division General Manager J.B. Damoose said
Chrysler likely will build the Viper two-seat sports car for the
1993 model year, although some engineering problems and financial
concerns are lingering.
   The car, to be powered by a V-10 or a V-8 engine with up to 400
horsepower, will sell at less than 5,000 a year, an extremely small
volume. By comparison, Mazda Motor Corp. is speculating that about
40,000 of its two-seat sports car Miata will be sold annually.
   Damoose said the Viper, first unveiled on the auto show circuit
in January, will cost between $25,000 and $30,000. The Miata has a
base price of $13,800.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
