<FIRST>r f BC-UpjohnRetirement     09-19 0164</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Upjohn Retirement,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Upjohn President Hoff to Retire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Upjohn Co. President and Chief Operating
Officer Lawrence C. Hoff will retire Jan. 1, the pharmaceutical
company said Tuesday.
   Upjohn Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Theodore Cooper will
assume the duties of president and hasn't announced plans to seek a
successor to Hoff, spokesman J.E. Galligan said.
   Hoff, 60, will remain on the Upjohn board, the company said.
   Hoff joined the company in 1950 as a pharmaceutical sales
representative. He became vice president of domestic pharmaceutical
marketing in 1969 and was elected to the board in 1973.
   He was promoted to executive vice president in 1977, elected
president of the company in 1984 and named chief operating officer
in 1987.
   Hoff is a board member of the Pharmaceutical Manufacturers
Association and served as its chairman in 1988.
   His retirement plans weren't a surprise, Galligan said. ``Mr.
Hoff had a 40-year career here,'' he said. ``He feels the company's
in good shape.''
</TEXT>
